The paper deals with analyzing large networks, which is a common problem in computer science. The use of graph mining methods and distributed systems suggests that the paper could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. The focus on communication cost and I/O costs suggests that the paper could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of execution strategies and partitioning suggests that the paper could belong to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
